  "conformsToProfile": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileMinimal",
  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded (axial compressive load 0–3000 N, bending moment 0–25 N·m, screw diameter 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm, UHMWPE block per ASTM F1717 geometry). Applicability constraint restricts use to non-cannulated designs only. Validation samples cover this envelope sparsely but gaps are honestly documented.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "modelRiskLevel": 3,
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "couName": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending",
